<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10570&amp;p=119356#p119356</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10570&amp;p=119356#p119356"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Most famous/popular PC games until the mid 90s]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10570&amp;p=119356#p119356"><![CDATA[
I hardly noticed this back in the day, but looking at some of these PC platformers now I'm amazed by how stiff the physics, sprite movement and scrolling are. I imagine that smooth scrolling would have made the games unplayable on older machines, which is probably why the games are like this, but when you compare them to what was available on consoles at the time, it's a surprise that anyone would want to play Hocus Pocus...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Mon Oct 14, 2013 6:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
